The paper deals with trajectory planning for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of real-time algorithms and optimization techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The comparison with existing approaches and the use of a high fidelity model suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
